1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,136
Iteration works better when the collaboration has rules.

2
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:07,961
Anthropic found that only thirty percent of conversations told Claude how the user wanted it to interact.

3
00:00:07,961 --> 00:00:13,182
Most people specified the task but left challenge, explanation, and uncertainty behavior implicit.

4
00:00:13,182 --> 00:00:15,548
Set those terms before the first answer.

5
00:00:15,548 --> 00:00:19,019
Tell the AI to push back when an assumption conflicts with evidence.

6
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:21,951
Ask it to name missing inputs before filling gaps.

7
00:00:21,951 --> 00:00:26,644
Require a brief rationale and the sources or observations that support consequential claims.

8
00:00:26,644 --> 00:00:29,192
Also define how uncertainty should appear.

9
00:00:29,192 --> 00:00:33,778
The AI can separate established facts, interpretations, and open questions.

10
00:00:33,778 --> 00:00:40,500
It can state confidence, show which input would change the conclusion, and stop when a missing permission or source would make continued work unsafe.

11
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,336
Then define acceptance.

12
00:00:42,336 --> 00:00:45,644
A draft is not done because it has all the requested sections.

13
00:00:45,644 --> 00:00:53,211
It is done when it matches the audience, respects the constraints, supports important claims, passes the relevant tests, and makes unresolved items visible.

14
00:00:53,211 --> 00:00:56,019
These instructions do not require a giant prompt.

15
00:00:56,019 --> 00:01:04,355
A compact collaboration contract can fit in four lines: challenge weak assumptions, surface missing context, support important claims, and mark uncertainty.

16
00:01:04,355 --> 00:01:07,346
Add task-specific acceptance criteria underneath.

17
00:01:07,346 --> 00:01:09,625
The contract changes the relationship.

18
00:01:09,625 --> 00:01:14,086
Instead of asking the AI to sound confident, you ask it to make confidence inspectable.

19
00:01:14,086 --> 00:01:19,346
Instead of rewarding immediate completion, you reward an output that helps you see where judgment is still required.

20
00:01:19,346 --> 00:01:23,259
First, tell the AI when to challenge assumptions and ask for context.

21
00:01:23,259 --> 00:01:27,586
Second, require visible grounds, uncertainty, and stop conditions.

22
00:01:27,586 --> 00:01:31,692
Third, define acceptance in terms of evidence and use rather than completeness.
